DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum Immunoglobulin Result Unspecified Upper Limit of Normal Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the upper limit of normal, units of measure not specified, for serum immunoglobulin, any of the structurally related glycoproteins that function as antibodies found in the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed, lab.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for serum immunoglobulin, any of the structurally related glycoproteins that function as antibodies found in the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: The clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed.:Glycoproteins present in the blood (ANTIBODIES) and in other tissue. They are classified by structure and activity into five classes (IMMUNOGLOBULIN A; IMMUNOGLOBULIN D; IMMUNOGLOBULIN E; IMMUNOGLOBULIN G; IMMUNOGLOBULIN M).:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: The clear portion of the blood that remains after the removal of the blood cells and the clotting proteins.
Any of the structurally related glycoproteins that function as antibodies. They are divided into five classes (IGA, IGD, IGE, IGG, IGM) on the basis of structure and biological activity.

ValueDomain.preferredName: Serum Immunoglobulin Unspecified Upper Limit of Normal Value
ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: information related to the unspecified upper limit of normal for immunoglobulin blood serum.
